<Content
  kicker="Blog · Trust & safety"
  title="Building a community of real people"
  lead="How verification, DM controls, and fast enforcement keep avaTOK genuine and safe."
  updated="2026-06-16"
>
  <p>
    Online spaces fall apart when no one knows who's real. Bots flood the feed, catfish fill the DMs,
    and the people most often targeted — especially women — pay the highest price. avaTOK is designed
    so that every account belongs to a real, verified human.
  </p>

  <h2>A video check at the door</h2>
  <p>
    To join gated areas, everyone completes a quick video identity check. A real person reviews
    liveness and approves the account. The result: no bots, no burner profiles, no fakes sliding into
    your messages.
  </p>

  <h2>You control your DMs</h2>
  <p>
    You decide exactly who can reach you. Blocking and reporting are one tap away, and we take reports
    seriously and act fast. Your space, your rules.
  </p>

  <h2>Safety isn't an afterthought</h2>
  <p>
    Women's safety is a first-class design goal, not a patch we added later. Our
    <a href="/community-guidelines">Community Guidelines</a> spell out what's expected, and our team
    enforces them.
  </p>

  <h2>Responsible AI, too</h2>
  <p>
    We use AI across avaTOK, and we use it carefully. AI can make mistakes, so we keep humans in the
    loop for sensitive decisions. We've also made our best efforts to use AI-generated imagery
    responsibly — if you ever find something objectionable, tell us at
    <a href="mailto:support@avatok.ai">support@avatok.ai</a> and we'll remove it.
  </p>

  <p>
    Real people, real respect. <a href="/">See how it works</a> or
    <a href="/contact">reach out</a>.
  </p>

  <p><a href="/blog">← Back to the blog</a></p>
</Content>
